The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, gave a speech at the Law & Justice event in Arlington, Virginia. He discussed various topics including the Trump administration's accomplishments in preserving the right to life, the state of religious freedom around the world, the importance of appointing conservative judges, the handling of attacks and criticism, the value of free speech, and the spiritual lessons he has learned as Vice President. Pence emphasized the administration's commitment to protecting the unborn, religious liberty, and the Constitution. He also highlighted the need for individuals to stand up for their beliefs and to focus on the positive aspects of their work.